=== Adjective ===

'''capricious'''

# [[impulsive]] and [[unpredictable]]; [[whimsical]]

Determined by chance, impulse, or whim; an action that lacks a rational basis.

Something that could change suddenly.

For example, "a capricious winter storm," or "stringent rulers often act capriciously."

